723267f-b.text:
68 to 60 South Street, west side, south from and including Pine, to
and including Wall Streets,  This block front, is now (1937), ocoupied
by the 120 Wall Street Building.
February 22, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
A part of the same, showing only Nos. 6B to 63, at, adjoining and  south of the S.W. corner of Pine Street.
February 22, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
The same as view No. 1, (but looking northward from Wall Street),
showing work in progress on the foundation for the No. 120 Wall Street Building. The creation of the site for the new building also necessitated the demolition of houses Nos. 120 to 114 Wall Street and Nos. 97 and 99 Pine Street.
May 13, 1929.
